HEADWORD: Schizopoda
<hw>Schi*zop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>, <ety>[NL.
See <er>Schizo-</er>, and <er>-poda</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A division of shrimplike Thoracostraca in which each of the
thoracic legs has a long fringed upper branch (exopodite) for
swimming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

